    {
      "label": "Recepten.se: Mått, vikt och enheter",
      "url": "https://www.recepten.se/artiklar/maatt_enheter.html",
      "used_for": [
        "1 krm = 1 ml",
        "1 tsk = 5 ml",
        "1 msk = 15 ml",
        "1 dl = 100 ml",
        "1 l = 1000 ml",
        "1 hg = 100 g",
        "1 kg = 1000 g"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    "This file is intended to be stricter than a freeform translation glossary. It preserves Swedish kitchen measurement semantics and flags ambiguous or culturally mixed units.",
    "For Swedish-native recipe notation, use Swedish kitchen standards where they exist: 1 krm = 1 ml, 1 tsk = 5 ml, 1 msk = 15 ml, 1 dl = 100 ml, 1 l = 1000 ml.",
    "Imperial and US customary units are included because imported Swedish recipes may still contain cup, oz, or lb from translated or internet-sourced material.",
    "Count, package, and size descriptors are separated from exact convertible units. They should not be silently converted to grams or milliliters without product-specific density assumptions.",
    "Ambiguous tokens should be flagged, not normalized blindly.",
    "Only the core Swedish measurement standards are externally verified here. Guard rules and importer policies are repository-level modeling choices."
  ],
